<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1230a: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Diplomatic Representatives in
                                    Colombia, Cuba, Mexico, and Uruguay</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-22T19:00:00-04:00">June 22, 1931—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>All the Governments having agreed on the text of the notes to be
                            delivered to Bolivia and Paraguay, the diplomatic representatives in
                            Washington of the neutral Governments have agreed with the Department
                            that the notes should be delivered to the Bolivian and Paraguayan
                            Governments on Thursday, June 25. Please so inform the Government to
                            which you are accredited.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>